The paper deals with the problem of computing correspondences between non-rigid shapes, which is a common problem in computer graphics and computer vision. The use of functional maps and spectral domain techniques suggests that the paper is likely to be related to computer vision and graphics, which are covered by the cs.CV and cs.GR categories. The paper also introduces a novel refinement technique, which involves optimization, suggesting that it may be related to optimization and machine learning, which are covered by the cs.LG category. The paper also deals with pointwise correspondences, which suggests that it may be related to computational geometry, covered by the cs.CG category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on challenging benchmarks, which suggests that it may be related to multimedia and image processing, covered by the cs.MM category.
